sVnews
p4
VA five-day music fest was jointly organised by Sama Gana Lahari and Avadhoot Sri Ganapathi Satchidananda Swamy Ashram in Vijayawada.Modumudi Sudhakar, a reputed vocalist and a staffer of A.I.R., Vijayawada, gave a gripping concert on the first day.  Sudhakar started withEndarothePancharatna KeertanainSri Ragamfollowing it with an elaborate rendition ofSimhendra Madhyamam. He also rendered a composition of Ganapathi Satchidananda SwamiGam Gam Ganapathiand a Ramadas KeertanaPaluke Bangaramayene. B.V.Durga Bhavani (violin), M.L.N.Raju(mridangam) and M.Haribabu (ghatam) provided good support .On the second day Mambalam sisters Vijayalakshmi and Chitra presented a pleasing vocal duet, they were supported by R.Hemalata on the violin (Chennai), Nellai Balaji on the mridangam (Chennai) and by K.Rangachari on the Kanjira (Chennai). The sisters provided a brisk start to the concert by singingMaha GanapatiminNatafollowed byPahi Pahi Gajananaa composition of Swamiji . The voices of the sisters blended melodiously and their traditional style was admired by the audience.  The concert also found place for a couple of Swamiji&#8217;s keertanas.Vishnubhotla sisters V. Saraswathi and V.Krishnaveni sang with vigour and showed fine command over themanodharmamaspects. They started withSidhi VinayakaminShanmukhapriyaThe main itemBantureetiinHamsanadamgot a detailed treatment . The sisters were ably followed by Palaparthi Nageswara Rao on violin, B.V.S. Prasad on the mridangam and Ramakrishna onghatam.D.Vardhani an accomplished singer from Hyderabad presented an engaging concert on the 4th day. . Vardhani began with avarnaminRanjaniand followed it withManasa Sancharare(Sama) and a Swamiji&#8217;s compositionGirijasutaminBouli. Another fine piece sung by Vardhani was GNB&#8217;sNeevalayimpainChayatarangini. Her raga elaboration andkalpana swaraswere highly impressive. She also rendered a composition of SwamijiBeejaksharaminHamsadhvani. The main itemNeevenannuinKambhojiwas well complimented Vardhani&#8217;s commandingragaalapanaandswaras.The fitting climax on the last day was an excellent concert by Malladi brothers Sriramprasad and Ravi Kumar and their father Malladi Suribabu. The popular trio started the concert withNada Tanum AnisaminChittaranjani,Gangadhara Sivam, a Swamiji&#8217;s composition and as the main item. The . The trio was supported well by P. Nageswara Rao (violin), N.S.Kalyanaraman (mridangam) and M.Haribabu (ghatam). It was a special day as Swamiji installed a Sphatika Sivaling in the huge ashram complex and performed special puja attended by thousands of devotees. Another highlight during the Malladi&#8217;s concert was the compositionRaghuvara Manohariof Ganapathi Satchidananda Swami tuned by them and rendered effectively.
